Review: The workers were amazing and very nice. The ambiance is pretty cool bc it was a foodhall. The food is what kept me from giving it a higher rating. I got the bandeja paisa and felt that the rice and beans were lacking flavor. The chorizo was not hitting, but the plantain was bomb. I would go again but to try the arepas.
The food was really good, the server was very nice and answered all questions. The portion sizes were also pretty big. They had a great variety of food.
